pull_request.body:
Bumps [com.nimbusds:nimbus-jose-jwt](https://bitbucket.org/connect2id/nimbus-jose-jwt) from 10.4 to 10.4.2.
Changelog

Sourced from com.nimbusds:nimbus-jose-jwt's changelog.

10.4 (2025-07-19) * Creates a hierarchy of Option interfaces, extended by JWSSignerOption, JWEEncrypterOption and JWEDecrypterOption. Intended to provide optional configuration parameters to RSASSASigner, ECDSASigner, RSADecrypter, etc. * Introduces CipherMode implementing JWEEncrypterOption and JWEDecrypterOption, to specify a preferred JCA Cipher mode, such as MODE_ENCRYPT / MODE_DECRYPT when the default MODE_WRAP / MODE_UNWRAP is not supported by the JCA provider (iss #576). * Updates RSAEncrypter and RSADecrypter to support the JWEEncrypterOption CipherMode.ENCRYPT_DECRYPT (iss #576). * Factors out OptionUtils.ensureMinRSAPrivateKeySize. * Deprecates OptionUtils.optionIsPresent.

10.4.1 (2025-08-05) * Adds "requires java.sql" to module com.nimbusds.jose.jwt (iss #595).

10.4.2 (2025-08-14) * Updates GSon to 2.13.1. * Updates BouncyCastle to 1.81.

issue.title: Docs: Incorrect venn diagram for anti right join
issue.body:
## Steps to reproduce

1. Open the PostgreSQL Joins tutorial page in Neon docs: https://neon.com/postgresql/postgresql-tutorial/postgresql-joins
2. Scroll to the **Right Anti-Join** section.
3. Observe the diagram shown.

## Expected result

The diagram should highlight **only the portion of the right table (T2) that does not overlap with the left table (T1)**, since Right Anti-Join returns rows from the right table without matches in the left table.

## Actual result

The diagram shown for **Right Anti-Join** is the same as the **Right Join** diagram, which incorrectly highlights the entire right table including the overlap.

## Environment

* Browser: zen-browser
* OS: kubuntu
* Page: https://neon.com/postgresql/postgresql-tutorial/postgresql-joins

## Logs, links

  Previously, some of Starlight‚Äôs remark and rehype plugins, most notably the plugin transforming Starlight's custom Markdown syntax for [rendering asides](https://starlight.astro.build/guides/authoring-content/#asides), were applied to all Markdown and MDX content.   This change restricts the application of Starlight‚Äôs remark and rehype plugins to only Markdown and MDX content loaded using Starlight's [`docsLoader()`](https://starlight.astro.build/reference/configuration/#docsloader). If you were relying on this behavior, please let us know about your use case in the dedicated `#starlight` channel in the [Astro Discord](https://astro.build/chat/) or by [opening an issue](https://redirect.github.com/withastro/starlight/issues/new?template=---01-bug-report.yml).
